data.title: 'Eastenders' Steve McFadden Becomes Dad Of Five As Girlfriend Karen Cairns 'Gives Birth To Baby Girl'
data.meta_description: The newborn's name has also been revealed.
data.text:
The newborn's name has also been revealed.

'Eastenders' actor Steve McFadden (a.k.a Phil Mitchell) has reportedly become a dad to his fifth child.

The 57-year-old's girlfriend Karen Cairns is said to have given birth to a baby girl named Frankie, according to The Sun.

"Steve and Karen are both over the moon with little Frankie," a source told the newspaper.

"Her pregnancy did come as a surprise, but now they are both really happy."

Advertisement

This is McFadden's first child with Cairns.

The actor is already dad to Matt, 28, with former partner Sue Marshall; Teona, 19, and Mollie Jane, 12, with Angela Bostock; and Amelie, seven, with Rachel Sidwell.

The news comes just days after McFadden won an "Outstanding Achievement" award at the British Soap Awards 2016.
